    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-08T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 8, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. For Duggan. It is now believed that, should the Department approve of again
                    presenting the matter of withdrawal of stamp in accordance with this morning’s
                    conversation and the Legation’s telegram No. 57, September 8, noon, it could be
                    handled more effectively through the Foreign Minister rather than direct with
                    the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Erwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
